ermany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 174, \"end\": 180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999481399987392, \"rank\": 5.186268819484603e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Senior Correspondent  During the USA men's Olympic basketball training camp in Las Vegas in early July,Stephen Currywas asked why he picked this moment to finally make his debut at the Games.\", \"from\": 200, \"to\": 391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 233, \"end\": 236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.7824965177263119, \"rank\": 0.17039400239804464, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 279, \"end\": 288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Valley\", \"score\": 0.9999043930879117, \"rank\": 9.476915871640535e-05, \"text\": \"Las Vegas\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Valley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Valley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back in 2012 and 2016, Curry reminded his inquisitor, the decision was made for him: he did not make the cut forLondon,after his third season in the NBA, and he skippedRiofour years later due to injuries.\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 596, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 541, \"end\": 544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9594646811427694e-32, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Curry could not even remember why he sat outTokyo-he's not alone in blocking out the COVID-19 days.\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 696, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Curry's public comments from 2021 suggest that he was\\u00a0 content to relax with his family that summer, pass on the hassle of those isolated and unattended Olympics, and look ahead to the upcoming 2022 season.\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  (Perhaps not coincidentally, Curry and the Golden State Warriors won the NBA title that year, the team's fourth of the Curry era.)\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 1050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 993, \"end\": 996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9594646811427694e-32, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am feeling as healthy as I have ever been,\\\" Curry told a group of reporters in Vegas, wearing a black bucket hat you might otherwise expect to see on a fishing boat.\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1220, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe the only positive of Golden State not making the playoffs this year: Curry had plenty of time to both rest and get ready for the Games.\", \"from\": 1221, \"to\": 1362, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1248, \"end\": 1260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golden_State_Warriors\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8401415239734226e-70, \"text\": \"Golden State\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golden_State_Warriors\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golden_State_Warriors\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then there is that none too small matter of age.\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1411, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's probably, realistically, my last opportunity to even have a chance to play,\\\" says Curry, 36.\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1511, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sure, Curry takes good care of himself.\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And his Olympic teammateLeBron Jamesis still going strong at 39.\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1616, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But if you are keen on experiencing the Olympics, you can not count on mimicking James' ageless play, and waiting for LA in 2028.\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1746, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1698, \"end\": 1703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7013238121481366e-22, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  \\\"It all kind of aligned the right way,\\\" says Curry.\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1814, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope it continues to align to a gold medal.\\\"\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1862, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost all of the all-time great men's basketball players have at least one of them, an Olympic gold medal.Michael Jordan,LeBron James,andKobe Bryantown a pair:Kevin Duranthas three.\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 2046, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1979, \"end\": 1985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jordan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.203140457248015e-30, \"text\": \"Jordan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jordan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jordan\"}, {\"begin\": 1986, \"end\": 1998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LeBron James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Larry Bird and Magic Johnson got theirs on the 1992 Dream Team; old-time legends like Bill Russell, Oscar Robertson, and the late Jerry West stood atop the podium.\", \"from\": 2047, \"to\": 2210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2047, \"end\": 2057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Bird\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Larry Bird\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Bird\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Bird\"}, {\"begin\": 2062, \"end\": 2075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magic_Johnson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.492822084698222e-49, \"text\": \"Magic Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magic_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magic_Johnson\"}, {\"begin\": 2094, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1992_United_States_men's_Olympic_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"1992 Dream Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1992_United_States_men's_Olympic_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1992_United_States_men's_Olympic_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2133, \"end\": 2145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bill_Russell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0305313405857627e-52, \"text\": \"Bill Russell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bill_Russell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bill_Russell\"}, {\"begin\": 2147, \"end\": 2162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Robertson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5031037546651143e-14, \"text\": \"Oscar Robertson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Robertson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Robertson\"}, {\"begin\": 2177, \"end\": 2187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerry_West\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jerry West\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerry_West\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerry_West\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps the top three U.S. players to never get a gold medal are Kareem Abdul-Jabbar, Wilt Chamberlain, and Curry.\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2325, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2276, \"end\": 2295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kareem_Abdul-Jabbar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kareem Abdul-Jabbar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kareem_Abdul-Jabbar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kareem_Abdul-Jabbar\"}, {\"begin\": 2297, \"end\": 2313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilt_Chamberlain\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wilt Chamberlain\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilt_Chamberlain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wilt_Chamberlain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Curry's definitely the lone 21st-century American super-duper star without one.\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2405, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2367, \"end\": 2375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.774535457258923, \"rank\": 0.2831231890779367, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's earned every other accolade in basketball.\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2454, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two-time NBA MVP.\", \"from\": 2455, \"to\": 2472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2464, \"end\": 2471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.946753005401396e-27, \"text\": \"NBA MVP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Four-time champion.\", \"from\": 2473, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"NBA Finals MVP, in 2022.\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2517, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2493, \"end\": 2507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBA Finals MVP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\"}, {\"begin\": 2493, \"end\": 2507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBA Finals MVP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And most important, the man who put a premium on three-point shooting, and single-handedly changed how basketball, America's most influential global sporting export, is played, from the NBA arenas on down to the dusty barns ofCYO.\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2704, \"end\": 2707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9594646811427694e-32, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  Read More:Simone Biles Is Still Dominating Gymnastics.\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's Also Changing It  \\\"This,\\\" says Warriors assistant coach and Curry confidante Bruce Fraser, referring to Curry's Olympic quest, \\\"is the final piece.\\\"\", \"from\": 2820, \"to\": 2974, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2903, \"end\": 2915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bruce_Fraser,_1st_Baron_Fraser_of_North_Cape\", \"score\": 0.9921637305491081, \"rank\": 0.0044934640522902155, \"text\": \"Bruce Fraser\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bruce_Fraser,_1st_Baron_Fraser_of_North_Cape\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bruce_Fraser,_1st_Baron_Fraser_of_North_Cape\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it's only fitting that he's joining forces with James in France.\", \"from\": 2976, \"to\": 3044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3028, \"end\": 3033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7013238121481366e-22, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 3037, \"end\": 3043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9781008071542554, \"rank\": 0.02116889751574893, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They battled for titles and alpha status over four straight Finals series, from 2015 to 2018, with Curry's Warriors getting the better of James' Cavs in three of those matchups.\", \"from\": 3045, \"to\": 3222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3183, \"end\": 3188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7013238121481366e-22, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Though one can argueDurant'sdefection from Oklahoma City to an already loaded Golden State team for the 2017 and 2018 championship runs did not quite make it a fair fight.)\", \"from\": 3223, \"to\": 3396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3267, \"end\": 3275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_Sooners_football\", \"score\": 0.9882162850359558, \"rank\": 0.01191403756171263, \"text\": \"Oklahoma\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_Sooners_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_Sooners_football\"}, {\"begin\": 3302, \"end\": 3314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golden_State_Warriors\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8401415239734226e-70, \"text\": \"Golden State\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golden_State_Warriors\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golden_State_Warriors\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We hated LeBron,\\\" says Fraser.\", \"from\": 3398, \"to\": 3429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3422, \"end\": 3428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Fraser\", \"score\": 0.9985629430144438, \"rank\": 0.000915115715017655, \"text\": \"Fraser\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Fraser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Fraser\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He hated us.\\\"\", \"from\": 3430, \"to\": 3444, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But six years after their last Finals battle, it's clearer than ever that both players benefitted from those duels.\", \"from\": 3445, \"to\": 3560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"James delivered on his ultimate promise: to bring Clevelandits first championship title, in any major pro sport, in 52 years.\", \"from\": 3561, \"to\": 3686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3561, \"end\": 3566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7013238121481366e-22, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That accomplishment placed him on a pinnacle, forever.\", \"from\": 3687, \"to\": 3741, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  Curry, meanwhile, led a dynasty.\", \"from\": 3743, \"to\": 3790, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At this point, the two players-born nearly four years apart at the same Akron, Ohio, hospital-can just enjoy their remaining matchups, and this precious time together as teammates.\", \"from\": 3791, \"to\": 3971, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3870, \"end\": 3874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio_University\", \"score\": 0.9050571136914403, \"rank\": 0.10406383181167546, \"text\": \"Ohio\", \"types\": [\"Q7075\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You can feel that they have a really true connection,\\\" says Fraser.\", \"from\": 3972, \"to\": 4040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4033, \"end\": 4039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Fraser\", \"score\": 0.9985629430144438, \"rank\": 0.000915115715017655, \"text\": \"Fraser\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Fraser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Fraser\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So they are very similar in their approach.\", \"from\": 4041, \"to\": 4085, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They work, they think, they strive for greatness.\\\"\", \"from\": 4086, \"to\": 4136, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read More:The IOC Wants the Olympics to Be Apolitical.\", \"from\": 4138, \"to\": 4192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's Impossible  Fraser worked out Curry at the Warriors facility in San Francisco as he geared up for the Games.\", \"from\": 4193, \"to\": 4308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4212, \"end\": 4218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Fraser\", \"score\": 0.9985629430144438, \"rank\": 0.000915115715017655, \"text\": \"Fraser\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Fraser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Fraser\"}, {\"begin\": 4264, \"end\": 4277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_49ers\", \"score\": 0.9989825776493066, \"rank\": 0.0009082226961549285, \"text\": \"San Francisco\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_49ers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_49ers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Curry primarily works with his longtime private trainer, Brandon Payne, in the offseason.)\", \"from\": 4309, \"to\": 4400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4367, \"end\": 4374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terrell_Brandon\", \"score\": 0.9993934115784421, \"rank\": 0.0006049637826533112, \"text\": \"Brandon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terrell_Brandon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terrell_Brandon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He could sense Curry's vigor for the task at hand.\", \"from\": 4401, \"to\": 4451, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The one thing that you do not see through the green eyes and the smile is the competitive spirit he has,\\\" says Fraser.\", \"from\": 4452, \"to\": 4571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4564, \"end\": 4570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Fraser\", \"score\": 0.9985629430144438, \"rank\": 0.000915115715017655, \"text\": \"Fraser\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Fraser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malcolm_Fraser\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's going to be going after it.\\\"\", \"from\": 4572, \"to\": 4606, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  The Americans, a comically talented team on paper-James, Curry, Durant, 2023 MVP Joel Embiid, recently crowned NBA champs Jason Tatum,Derrick White,and Jrue Holiday, Anthony Davis, emerging superstar Anthony Edwards, etc.-will still need to learn to mesh.\", \"from\": 4608, \"to\": 4878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4623, \"end\": 4636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.341000409880444e-25, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 4734, \"end\": 4737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9594646811427694e-32, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 4745, \"end\": 4750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"score\": 0.936570413771345, \"rank\": 0.06748670293648117, \"text\": \"Jason\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\"}, {\"begin\": 4751, \"end\": 4756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Art_Tatum\", \"score